Douglas DC-5-510 c/n 424, seen here as KLM West Indies PJ-AIW 'Wakago'.  Ex G-AFYI, PH-AXA, later PK-ADD with KNILM, then to the Australian civil registry as VH-CXB.  It was damaged in a forced landing on November 6, 1942 east of Charleville, Qld, Australia, and used for spares for VH-CXC.  At one point it received the USAAF designation C-110-DE serial number 44-83231.

According to <a href="http://www.ruudleeuw.com/dc5-pjaiw-history.htm" rel="nofollow">this online history</a>, this aircraft &quot;...whilst on a goodwill visit to Australia in April 1941 had the distinction of being the first aircraft in Australia to have a nosewheel...&quot; 


See another photo in these markings <a href="http://www.ruudleeuw.com/tmp-dc5-pjaiw.jpg" rel="nofollow">here</a>.
